article.headline: Idaho 76, Hawaii 75
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho (AP) -- Clyde Johnson sank a 3-point field goal with less than a second left Thursday night to give Idaho a 76-75 victory over Hawaii. Keoni Watson led Idaho (3-14, 1-4 Western Athletic Conference) with 16 points, including a 3-pointer that tied the game at 73-all with 11.5 seconds to go. Johnson scored a season-high 15 points, Darin Nagle also had 15 points and Desmond Nwoke had a career-high 14 points. Dominic Waters led Hawaii (10-8, 1-4 WAC) with a career-high 18 points. Matt Lojeski added 17 points and Ahmet Gueye had 15 points, 14 rebounds and four blocked shots. Johnson's game-winning basket gave the Vandals their first lead since going ahead 28-27 with 8:38 left in the first half. The Vandals had dropped four consecutive games overall and 12 straight WAC games. Hawaii, 0-5 on the road this season, took a 75-73 lead when Waters sank two free throws with 8.7 seconds to go. Gueye went 11 for 14 at the free-throw line, including 6 for 8 in the final four minutes. Watson, Idaho's leading scorer with 17 points per game, finished 5 for 19 from the field. The Vandals, who made a season-low seven turnovers, trailed 40-35 at the half.
